{
  "page_type": "function",
  "name": "IpGetLastSocketError",
  "category": "TCPIPAPI",
  "title": "IpGetLastSocketError",
  "source": "chm_extract_v15/CANoeCANalyzer/Topics/CAPLFunctions/TCPIPAPI/Functions/CAPLfunctionIPGetLastSocketError.htm",
  "syntax": [
    "long IpGetLastSocketError( dword socket);"
  ],
  "description": [
    "The function returns the Winsock 2 error code of the last operation that failed on the specified socket."
  ],
  "parameters": [
    {
      "name": "socket",
      "type": "",
      "description": "The socket handle."
    }
  ],
  "return": "",
  "example": {
    "description": [],
    "code": "on start\n{\n  const dword INVALID_SOCKET = ~0; // invalid socket constant\n  dword socket = INVALID_SOCKET;   // a socket\n\n  // just create an unspecified socket.\n  socket = UdpOpen( 0, 0 );\n\n  // produce an error e.g. using invalid parameters to UdpSendTo\n  if (UdpSendTo(socket, 0, 0, \"a\", 1) == -1)\n  {\n    writeLineEx(1, 3, \"IpGetLastSocketError: %d\", IpGetLastSocketError(socket));\n  }\n\n  // close the socket.\n  UdpClose(socket);\n}"
  },
